1
00:02:28,911 --> 00:02:31,630
Do you know
what he said to me last time?

2
00:02:31,747 --> 00:02:34,500
I said to him,
"Are you the jolliest at home?"

3
00:02:34,625 --> 00:02:38,721
And he said, "Yes, except for the doorknob
because that gives everyone a handshake."

4
00:02:38,838 --> 00:02:39,839
Oh!

5
00:05:37,016 --> 00:05:38,142
Oi!

6
00:05:59,788 --> 00:06:03,588
Aye, aye, me damsel.

7
00:06:03,709 --> 00:06:05,382
Welcome home, Mr Billy.

8
00:06:09,298 --> 00:06:11,642
- We've been worried to death about you.
- For why?

9
00:06:11,759 --> 00:06:13,352
On account of that explosion,

10
00:06:13,469 --> 00:06:15,722
- What was that?
- At Ostend.

11
00:06:15,846 --> 00:06:19,020
Oh, yes.
I heard tell of that at Antwerp.

12
00:06:19,141 --> 00:06:20,393
Dreadful.

13
00:06:20,851 --> 00:06:21,898
Dirty linen.

14
00:06:22,019 --> 00:06:24,363
Mr William's been getting
in a stew about it.

15
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:27,654
- Is he out and about his business?
- That he is.

16
00:06:59,932 --> 00:07:02,185
You faring well?

17
00:07:02,309 --> 00:07:03,731
Thank you.

18
00:07:08,816 --> 00:07:11,786
- How was your journey home?
- It was execrable.

19
00:07:11,902 --> 00:07:13,154
Oh.

20
00:07:37,136 --> 00:07:39,764
You in need of anything else?

21
00:07:39,888 --> 00:07:41,105
Tea?

22
00:08:09,084 --> 00:08:13,089
- Good morning, Signor Grande.
- Mr Turner! Buongiorno.

23
00:08:13,213 --> 00:08:14,556
- Joshua.
- Morning, sir.

24
00:08:14,673 --> 00:08:16,767
We have damn rats.

25
00:08:16,884 --> 00:08:18,477
No shortage of them in this city.

26
00:08:18,594 --> 00:08:22,098
Wretched things!
It's an epidemic.

27
00:08:22,222 --> 00:08:24,896
- What can I do for you today?
- Well, let me see.

28
00:08:25,017 --> 00:08:27,770
- He is back?
- We are expecting him any day now.

29
00:08:27,895 --> 00:08:30,239
<i>Bravo!</i> The prodigal son.

30
00:08:30,355 --> 00:08:33,529
- <i>Pronti.</i> What do we need?
- An ounce of chrome yellow.

31
00:08:33,650 --> 00:08:35,744
- Chrome yellow, Joshua,
- Chrome yellow, sir.

32
00:08:35,861 --> 00:08:38,455
- A large packet of ﬂake white.
- Flake white.

33
00:08:39,364 --> 00:08:41,992
What is your price
for a bladder of ultramarine?

34
00:08:42,117 --> 00:08:43,915
My price is the best price.

35
00:08:44,036 --> 00:08:46,164
And what might that price be?

36
00:08:46,288 --> 00:08:50,759
Blue ultramarine is coming
from far, far away: Afghanistan.

37
00:08:50,876 --> 00:08:54,255
- What else do you need?
- Bottle of poppy oil, some Indian red.

38
00:08:54,379 --> 00:08:56,723
- Poppy oil, Joshua.
- Yes, sir.

39
00:09:31,333 --> 00:09:33,711
There's your prize porker.

40
00:09:33,835 --> 00:09:35,758
Is he handsome?

41
00:09:35,879 --> 00:09:38,302
He has a big smile on his face.

42
00:09:39,633 --> 00:09:42,557
- You're making the sauce?
- It's all but done, save the brains.

43
00:09:42,678 --> 00:09:45,682
Good.
Oh... dearie me!

44
00:09:45,806 --> 00:09:49,856
- Will you take a dish of tea, Mr William?
- Oh, thank ye, Hannah.

45
00:09:49,977 --> 00:09:52,901
Shall you be putting those chattels away?
I should.

46
00:09:53,021 --> 00:09:54,694
- Best do it now.
- Yes.

47
00:09:54,815 --> 00:09:57,819
Then I can rest me weary legs.

48
00:10:16,545 --> 00:10:19,424
You're home, Billy boy!

49
00:10:22,384 --> 00:10:24,887
Hey, Daddy!

50
00:10:26,346 --> 00:10:28,223
I thought you was exploded.

51
00:10:28,348 --> 00:10:31,067
I been down on my knees
and praying you was safe.

52
00:10:31,184 --> 00:10:34,233
Well, you been chafing your old pedestals
for naught, Daddy.

53
00:10:34,354 --> 00:10:35,651
I was a hundred miles distant.

54
00:10:35,772 --> 00:10:37,695
- Oh, you heard tell of it, then?
- I did indeed.

55
00:10:37,816 --> 00:10:41,241
Terrible, they pour souls as perished,
two score or more.

56
00:10:41,361 --> 00:10:44,490
Took a few brave soldiers with it an' all.

57
00:10:44,614 --> 00:10:48,164
I was vexed to learn
you been entertaining concerns, old Dadda.

58
00:10:48,285 --> 00:10:50,253
'Twas only natural.

59
00:10:51,538 --> 00:10:53,666
Oh, Daddy!

60
00:10:53,790 --> 00:10:55,463
How was your crossing?

61
00:10:55,584 --> 00:10:58,838
Set fair on departure,
lumpy in the middle.

62
00:10:58,962 --> 00:11:01,886
- Did you sail from Rotterdam?
- No, Dieppe.

63
00:11:02,007 --> 00:11:03,475
Oh.

64
00:11:03,592 --> 00:11:06,471
Night coach from Brighton
proved to be an heinous travail.

65
00:11:06,595 --> 00:11:07,517
How so?

66
00:11:07,637 --> 00:11:10,356
It was stuffed full of yacking
and cackling females.

67
00:11:10,474 --> 00:11:14,229
Pox-ridden harridan as broad in the beam
as the old Victory at Trafalgar.

68
00:11:14,353 --> 00:11:19,029
- Were your travels productive?
- Exceeding refreshing, old Daddy.

69
00:11:19,149 --> 00:11:20,571
Yeah, Amsterdam.

70
00:11:20,692 --> 00:11:23,161
Had a gander at the Rembrandt.

71
00:11:23,278 --> 00:11:25,827
Militia Company, Antwerp Cathedral.

72
00:11:25,947 --> 00:11:27,745
Rubens, the triptych.

73
00:11:27,866 --> 00:11:30,244
Flanders, still as ﬂat as a witch's tit.

74
00:11:30,369 --> 00:11:33,748
Thank you, Hannah.
You sly girl.

75
00:11:35,332 --> 00:11:37,585
Did you find tolerable diggings?

76
00:11:37,709 --> 00:11:40,804
Stinking ﬂea pit at Dieppe,
then moved to the harbour.

77
00:11:40,921 --> 00:11:43,515
Westerly aspect, fine sunset.

78
00:11:43,632 --> 00:11:46,351
Oh, Daddy,
I'm in need of an eight-by-six.

79
00:11:46,468 --> 00:11:51,315
I have a seven by five-and-a-half
ready sized and primed.

80
00:11:51,431 --> 00:11:54,105
- That should suit,
- Right you be.

81
00:11:54,226 --> 00:11:57,070
More's to the point,
how you been faring?

82
00:11:57,187 --> 00:11:58,780
In good health, thank the Lord.

83
00:11:58,897 --> 00:12:01,150
- Bronchioles still rattling?
- No.

84
00:12:01,274 --> 00:12:03,572
- He was wheezing last week.
- Shh-sh-sh,

85
00:12:03,693 --> 00:12:07,163
October ain't quite come
round the corner yet, has it?

86
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:09,032
I've been over to Grande's.

87
00:12:09,157 --> 00:12:10,204
Oh.

88
00:12:10,325 --> 00:12:12,578
Ultramarine's gone up
to a guinea a bladder.

89
00:12:12,702 --> 00:12:13,999
Gawd's truth!

90
00:12:14,121 --> 00:12:16,089
That brigand still robbing us, is he?

91
00:12:17,374 --> 00:12:22,175
- You're in need of a shave.
- Yeah, well, be that as it may, Daddy.

92
00:12:22,295 --> 00:12:26,391
Presently I'm gonna throw myself
into the arms of Morpheus.

93
00:13:09,509 --> 00:13:10,726
No!

94
00:13:21,354 --> 00:13:24,198
I took a trip down west, Exeter, last week.

95
00:13:24,316 --> 00:13:25,943
Oh.

96
00:13:26,067 --> 00:13:29,446
- How fares the old uncle?
- Bearing up, considering.

97
00:13:29,571 --> 00:13:33,371
- Considering what?
- Well, his age, living alone.

98
00:13:33,492 --> 00:13:34,539
Oh.

99
00:13:38,455 --> 00:13:40,298
- Here's the thing.
- Hm?

100
00:13:40,415 --> 00:13:43,168
He wants to arrange a family gathering.

101
00:14:01,311 --> 00:14:03,814
Will you take some more cheek?

102
00:14:03,939 --> 00:14:07,193
Yeah, cast us another morsel.

103
00:14:07,317 --> 00:14:10,116
Missing your button, Mr Billy.

104
00:14:10,237 --> 00:14:11,784
Oh.

105
00:14:25,835 --> 00:14:29,339
Be so kind as to enter the vestibule.

106
00:14:37,180 --> 00:14:40,184
The darkness is to a purpose.

107
00:14:41,017 --> 00:14:43,861
I shall return by and by.

108
00:15:10,755 --> 00:15:12,177
Madam.

109
00:15:14,092 --> 00:15:15,514
Gentlemen.

110
00:15:21,224 --> 00:15:22,726
Behold.

111
00:15:28,607 --> 00:15:30,609
Three steps down.

112
00:15:41,244 --> 00:15:43,588
Pray, view at your leisure.

113
00:16:17,364 --> 00:16:19,605
- Good day to you, Hannah.
- Good day to you, Aunt Sarah.

114
00:16:19,658 --> 00:16:22,127
- And how are you faring?
- Very well, thank you.

115
00:16:22,243 --> 00:16:24,587
- Are you coming in?
- I most certainly am. Is he at home?

116
00:16:24,704 --> 00:16:27,924
- He is. I'll tell him you're here.
- I can inform him myself, thank you kindly.

117
00:16:30,502 --> 00:16:34,177
- Good day to you, sir.
- And a very good day to you, Mrs D.

118
00:16:34,297 --> 00:16:36,516
And how do we find you
on this fair morning?

119
00:16:36,633 --> 00:16:38,852
Exceedingly preoccupied, madam.

120
00:16:38,968 --> 00:16:41,517
'Twas ever thus.
You've always been preoccupied.

121
00:16:41,638 --> 00:16:43,686
You're too preoccupied
for your own good, sir.

122
00:16:43,807 --> 00:16:45,650
Nothing comes from nothing, madam.

123
00:16:45,767 --> 00:16:48,145
And we have had nothing from you, sir.

124
00:16:49,979 --> 00:16:52,778
Evelina, Georgiana,
come and greet your father.

125
00:16:52,899 --> 00:16:56,369
Good day, Father.
May I present my child to you?

126
00:16:56,486 --> 00:16:58,659
- Your granddaughter'
- Rosalie Adelaide.

127
00:16:58,780 --> 00:17:00,953
Your only surviving grandchild.

128
00:17:01,074 --> 00:17:03,327
Georgiana, cease your dithering!

129
00:17:03,451 --> 00:17:06,000
May I suggest, Mrs D,
with the utmost respect,

130
00:17:06,121 --> 00:17:09,045
that you withdraw
to the drawing room?

131
00:17:09,165 --> 00:17:12,135
Good day to you, Mrs Danby.
Would you care to step this way?

132
00:17:12,252 --> 00:17:13,879
Good day to you, Mr Turner.

133
00:17:14,003 --> 00:17:15,763
And will you be gracing us
with your presence

134
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:17,882
in the withdrawing room, sir?

135
00:17:18,007 --> 00:17:21,011
I sincerely hope you will.
And, pray, do not keep us waiting.

136
00:17:21,136 --> 00:17:23,935
We have our own lives to lead.
Come along, daughters.

137
00:17:24,055 --> 00:17:27,355
The vapours in this room
are most noxious to a child's lungs.

138
00:17:38,653 --> 00:17:41,156
Ladies, pray, sit yourselves.

139
00:17:42,365 --> 00:17:43,582
Sarah, if you please.

140
00:17:43,700 --> 00:17:46,749
I shall be seated, William,
when it suits me and not before.

141
00:17:46,870 --> 00:17:48,292
So be it.

142
00:17:49,330 --> 00:17:52,174
- She's a pretty little thing.
- Thank you, Grandfather.

143
00:17:52,292 --> 00:17:54,636
- We are most proud of her.
- We are indeed.

144
00:17:54,753 --> 00:17:57,176
- Have you been out strolling, Aunt Sarah?
- No, niece.

145
00:17:57,297 --> 00:17:59,425
I've been to collect my pension
at Leicester Fields,

146
00:17:59,549 --> 00:18:01,096
it being the first of the month.

147
00:18:01,217 --> 00:18:05,142
Indeed.

148
00:18:05,263 --> 00:18:07,231
- Your latest infant?
- To be sure, Father.

149
00:18:07,348 --> 00:18:09,817
- Of robust constitution?
- She has an excellent character.

150
00:18:09,934 --> 00:18:12,778
One must trust in providence.
Colour of eye?

151
00:18:12,896 --> 00:18:14,864
- Blue, as yourself.
- Splendid.

152
00:18:14,981 --> 00:18:16,699
Do not forget your other daughter, sir,

153
00:18:16,816 --> 00:18:19,285
whom you have deigned to neglect
these past two years.

154
00:18:19,402 --> 00:18:21,245
Sit down, Georgiana.

155
00:18:21,362 --> 00:18:23,785
- She is learning French.
- And music.

156
00:18:23,907 --> 00:18:25,705
She is having an education.

157
00:18:25,825 --> 00:18:29,830
Reading, writing, arithmetic
and geography with the globe.

158
00:18:29,954 --> 00:18:31,547
Sit up straight, Georgie!

159
00:18:31,664 --> 00:18:33,211
Say something in French.

160
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:34,926
<i>- Bonjour.
- Bonjour, Papa.</i>

161
00:18:36,085 --> 00:18:37,632
- Are you keeping well?
- I am.

162
00:18:37,754 --> 00:18:39,631
I was not addressing you, sir.

163
00:18:39,756 --> 00:18:42,259
I enjoy good health, thank'ee.
And yourself?

164
00:18:42,383 --> 00:18:45,478
We are surviving as best we can
under the circumstances.

165
00:18:45,595 --> 00:18:49,645
- And what circumstances might they be?
- Straightened circumstances, sir.

166
00:18:49,766 --> 00:18:51,643
But we manage
to keep body and soul together,

167
00:18:51,768 --> 00:18:54,612
no thanks to your ungrateful son.

168
00:18:55,355 --> 00:18:58,154
How dare you take your leave of me,
Billy Turner!

169
00:18:58,274 --> 00:19:02,450
You insult me,
as you have always insulted me!

170
00:19:02,570 --> 00:19:03,992
Billy!

171
00:19:43,236 --> 00:19:44,533
Good evening, William.

172
00:19:44,654 --> 00:19:47,498
Felicitations of the evening to you,
your Lordship.

173
00:19:48,408 --> 00:19:50,536
You faring well?

174
00:19:50,660 --> 00:19:54,255
Bit breathless.
Been up to the farm.

175
00:19:57,458 --> 00:20:00,803
Watch the sunset,
say goodnight to the milkmaids.

176
00:20:02,088 --> 00:20:05,262
Any further consideration
to mechanicalising the thresher?

177
00:20:08,052 --> 00:20:09,895
You can't beat the old oxen.

178
00:20:10,013 --> 00:20:13,358
- Is that so, your Lordship?
- Indeed.

179
00:20:13,474 --> 00:20:16,648
We had a ploughing competition
last spring

180
00:20:16,769 --> 00:20:19,568
between teams of horses
and teams of oxen.

181
00:20:19,689 --> 00:20:21,691
- And the victor?
- The horses.

182
00:20:21,816 --> 00:20:25,320
- Well, the ox is a sluggish beast
- Yes, but strong.

183
00:20:25,445 --> 00:20:28,039
With the added benefit, when it comes
to the end of its working life,

184
00:20:28,156 --> 00:20:29,999
it makes a very succulent dish.

185
00:20:31,576 --> 00:20:33,249
Unlike the horse.

186
00:20:33,369 --> 00:20:34,370
Good for glue.

187
00:20:34,495 --> 00:20:36,998
Ahem... your Lordship!

188
00:20:39,584 --> 00:20:42,804
- A very good evening to you, sir.
- Evening, Manners.

189
00:20:42,921 --> 00:20:45,174
Mr Turner.

190
00:20:46,174 --> 00:20:48,142
Are we not blessed by the heavens

191
00:20:48,259 --> 00:20:54,437
to witness so glorious
a crepuscular time of day?

192
00:20:57,143 --> 00:20:58,690
Imbecile.

193
00:21:02,732 --> 00:21:07,363
Continuing satisfaction
as to the arrangement, your Lordship?

194
00:21:07,487 --> 00:21:12,994
I think we have successfully achieved
the correct effect, William.

195
00:21:13,117 --> 00:21:14,619
Thank you.

196
00:21:16,829 --> 00:21:20,049
- Good evening, Nat.
- Oh, good evening, my Lord.

197
00:21:20,166 --> 00:21:24,637
- Good evening, Miss Coggins.
- Your Lordship, Turner.

198
00:21:24,754 --> 00:21:28,384
- How's your father faring, William?
- Oh, bearing up, your Lordship.

199
00:21:28,508 --> 00:21:31,136
Very gracious of you to inquire.

200
00:21:31,260 --> 00:21:35,185
We thought we'd lost him
this last winter, a very harsh one.

201
00:21:35,306 --> 00:21:37,934
He came through.
He's a hardy old cove.

202
00:21:38,059 --> 00:21:39,561
Excellent.

203
00:21:40,269 --> 00:21:42,522
- See you at dinner.
- Indeed.

204
00:22:29,485 --> 00:22:31,783
Exceedingly beautiful.

205
00:22:31,904 --> 00:22:33,906
You are too kind.

206
00:22:34,490 --> 00:22:37,619
I'm familiar with the melody, but...

207
00:22:37,744 --> 00:22:39,792
- Herr Beethoven.
- Ah!

208
00:22:39,912 --> 00:22:41,380
The "Pathétique".

209
00:22:49,338 --> 00:22:53,218
I possess a rare fondness
for... Henry Purcell.

210
00:22:54,969 --> 00:22:55,970
As do I.

211
00:22:56,095 --> 00:22:57,688
Oh?

212
00:22:57,805 --> 00:22:59,227
Um...

213
00:23:02,101 --> 00:23:03,227
Yes.

214
00:23:09,192 --> 00:23:11,615
“Dido-s Lament."

215
00:23:17,992 --> 00:23:21,496
♪ May my wrongs create

216
00:23:21,621 --> 00:23:23,294
♪ Create

217
00:23:23,414 --> 00:23:25,837
♪ No sorrow...

218
00:23:25,958 --> 00:23:27,050
- Trouble.
- ♪ Trou...

219
00:23:27,168 --> 00:23:29,842
♪ No trouble

220
00:23:29,962 --> 00:23:33,057
♪ In thy breast... thy breast...
- Thy breast.

221
00:23:33,174 --> 00:23:36,804
♪ In thy bream breast

222
00:23:41,933 --> 00:23:45,858
♪ Remember me

223
00:23:48,397 --> 00:23:51,492
♪ Remember me

224
00:23:54,529 --> 00:23:56,406
♪ But...

225
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:59,368
- Ah! Forget my fate.
- ♪ Ah!

226
00:23:59,492 --> 00:24:03,042
♪ Forget my fate

227
00:24:04,872 --> 00:24:10,094
♪ Remember me

228
00:24:10,378 --> 00:24:12,676
♪ But ah!

229
00:24:12,797 --> 00:24:16,802
♪ Forget my fa...

230
00:24:18,344 --> 00:24:20,017
♪ My fate ♪

231
00:24:27,812 --> 00:24:29,860
A song of lost love.

232
00:24:31,649 --> 00:24:33,651
Indeed.

233
00:24:35,820 --> 00:24:37,697
I thank you.

234
00:24:37,822 --> 00:24:40,325
Thank you, Mr Turner.

235
00:24:42,660 --> 00:24:44,082
Madam.

236
00:25:07,935 --> 00:25:09,357
Shh-sh-sh!

237
00:25:22,491 --> 00:25:24,585
- Mr Turner?
- Hm?

238
00:25:24,702 --> 00:25:27,626
I have often pondered,
might there be a distinction

239
00:25:27,747 --> 00:25:31,092
between the way you paint a sunrise
as opposed to a sunset?

240
00:25:31,209 --> 00:25:34,179
- Oh, there is indeed, Lady Stuckley.
- Ah.

241
00:25:34,295 --> 00:25:37,265
Yeah, cos one is going up
whilst the other...

242
00:25:37,381 --> 00:25:39,634
- The other is going down!
- Oh, Eliza, do hush.

243
00:25:39,759 --> 00:25:44,060
And might it also be determined
by the angle of the light?

244
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:46,899
Well, it's weather,

245
00:25:47,016 --> 00:25:48,359
vapour,

246
00:25:48,476 --> 00:25:49,602
wind.

247
00:25:49,727 --> 00:25:51,855
Frangibility and such like.

248
00:25:51,979 --> 00:25:53,356
- Eliza, look at his nails!
- Shh.

249
00:25:53,481 --> 00:25:57,236
Whilst you goddesses are languishing
in the kingdom of Hypnos,

250
00:25:57,360 --> 00:26:01,365
I am up before the lark to witness Helios
popping his head above the parapet,

251
00:26:01,489 --> 00:26:05,335
with the only benefit
that the sunrise is not afﬂicted...

252
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:08,083
...with diminishing light.

253
00:26:16,712 --> 00:26:18,510
- Carew.
- Oh!

254
00:26:18,631 --> 00:26:20,383
Turner!

255
00:26:20,508 --> 00:26:23,853
I'm by way of observing
poor Saint Sebastian here.

256
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:26,393
The artist is not known to me.

257
00:26:26,514 --> 00:26:27,811
- Flemish.
- Oh.

258
00:26:27,932 --> 00:26:30,902
Uncommonly capacious rump
on the cherub.

259
00:26:31,018 --> 00:26:33,942
It might have gained in potency
with an increase of arrows.

260
00:26:34,063 --> 00:26:36,441
Well, yon celestial fellow
is tugging them all out.

261
00:26:36,565 --> 00:26:37,987
I can hardly bear to look upon it.

262
00:26:38,109 --> 00:26:43,036
Ah, the pain on his face,
the mark of resignation in it.

263
00:26:43,155 --> 00:26:45,283
'Tis a willing sacrifice, is it not?

264
00:26:45,408 --> 00:26:47,877
'Twas not how the poor soul perished.

265
00:26:47,994 --> 00:26:50,998
He was brought back to full health
by a good Samaritan.

266
00:26:51,122 --> 00:26:54,797
Then the heathens cudgelled him to death
and deposited him in a sewer.

267
00:26:54,917 --> 00:26:57,636
I would question
the veracity of that telling.

268
00:26:57,753 --> 00:27:00,097
No good deed goes unpunished.

269
00:27:04,885 --> 00:27:06,887
What a curious fate is mine.

270
00:27:08,556 --> 00:27:12,436
Last month in the King's Bench Prison
in the company of debtors,

271
00:27:12,560 --> 00:27:15,109
this month a guest
of quality, rank and fashion.

272
00:27:15,229 --> 00:27:19,325
Rejoice, Haydon. You find yourself
in a veritable Bacchanalia.

273
00:27:19,442 --> 00:27:22,662
His Lordship keeps
a very fine wine cellar.

274
00:27:22,778 --> 00:27:24,951
Be sanguine, fill your boots.

275
00:27:25,072 --> 00:27:26,873
Might I ask you
to loan me some money, Turner?

276
00:27:26,907 --> 00:27:28,124
I beg your pardon?

277
00:27:28,242 --> 00:27:31,712
I am in dire and pressing need
of 100 pounds.

278
00:27:31,829 --> 00:27:33,001
Out of the question.

279
00:27:33,122 --> 00:27:35,716
My landlord,
he's a good man, a patient man,

280
00:27:35,833 --> 00:27:37,676
but he will not wait forever.

281
00:27:37,793 --> 00:27:40,592
I need to pay the wine merchant,
my colour man...

282
00:27:40,713 --> 00:27:43,387
And your dear wife, Mrs Haydon,
is she faring well?

283
00:27:43,507 --> 00:27:45,384
Mrs Haydon is presently with child.

284
00:27:45,509 --> 00:27:47,853
Well, you have my hearty congratulations,
Haydon.

285
00:27:47,970 --> 00:27:51,600
Congratulations are not in order.
I'm in torment.

286
00:27:51,724 --> 00:27:55,354
I am not unsympathetic
to your impecunity, Haydon.

287
00:27:55,478 --> 00:27:58,277
Therefore I can advance you 50 pounds.

288
00:27:58,397 --> 00:28:02,277
Turner, if 100 pounds will not spare me
from this predicament,

289
00:28:02,401 --> 00:28:04,745
what in Jesu's name
can 50 pounds do?

290
00:28:04,862 --> 00:28:07,581
Then you are refusing
to accept the 50 pounds?

291
00:28:07,698 --> 00:28:10,918
- It is damned inadequate,
- I wish you good day, sir.

292
00:28:15,164 --> 00:28:16,791
- Turner?
- Hey, hey!

293
00:28:16,916 --> 00:28:19,169
My word is my bond.

294
00:28:19,293 --> 00:28:22,763
I may not yet be an Academician
but I am a gentleman.

295
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:25,724
I have a painting
presently with the King at Windsor.

296
00:28:25,841 --> 00:28:29,186
I am assured he will buy it from me
for 500 guineas or more.

297
00:28:29,303 --> 00:28:31,852
Furthermore, I have another
fine painting in mind,

298
00:28:31,972 --> 00:28:33,098
a companion piece,

299
00:28:33,224 --> 00:28:35,147
which he is most certain
to purchase in addition.

300
00:28:35,267 --> 00:28:37,361
Who has made these assurances?

301
00:28:37,478 --> 00:28:40,231
- The King's private secretary, Knighton.
- Oh.

302
00:28:40,356 --> 00:28:45,487
Well, I can furnish you
with five pounds this morning.

303
00:28:45,611 --> 00:28:46,863
Five pounds?

304
00:28:46,987 --> 00:28:50,287
50 pounds is not sufficient.
Five pounds is tantamount to an insult.

305
00:28:50,408 --> 00:28:53,537
Sir, I beseech you, brook your ire.

306
00:28:53,661 --> 00:28:56,210
If you attend my residence at London,

307
00:28:56,330 --> 00:28:58,583
I will loan you 50 pounds.

308
00:28:59,834 --> 00:29:01,836
In addition to the five?

309
00:29:02,837 --> 00:29:06,558
Mr Haydon, you are exceedingly tiresome.

310
00:29:09,885 --> 00:29:12,138
I am gratified.

311
00:29:13,472 --> 00:29:16,567
I humbly accept the 50 pounds.

312
00:29:18,144 --> 00:29:21,444
Might I find you at the same address?

313
00:29:23,566 --> 00:29:25,068
I may swim.

314
00:29:28,404 --> 00:29:31,578
"And the spirit immediately
drove him out into the wilderness."

315
00:29:31,699 --> 00:29:34,418
A tormented soul, for sure.

316
00:29:34,535 --> 00:29:37,914
I sympathise,
but he attributes all of his failures

317
00:29:38,038 --> 00:29:40,507
- to anything other than his own behaviour.
- Indeed.

318
00:29:40,624 --> 00:29:45,551
His complaint with life is as absurd
as that of a spoke in a wheel,

319
00:29:45,671 --> 00:29:49,221
railing against the motion
that it must of necessity partake.

320
00:29:49,341 --> 00:29:53,221
I concur.
He suffers the fate of Tantalus.

321
00:29:53,345 --> 00:29:56,315
He reaches for the fruit,
the branch moves.

322
00:29:56,432 --> 00:29:59,026
When he stoops to drink
the water goes down.

323
00:29:59,143 --> 00:30:01,896
If only he would consider
the wishes of his public

324
00:30:02,021 --> 00:30:05,366
rather than pursuing
his own peculiar convictions,

325
00:30:05,483 --> 00:30:06,609
it would be his salvation.

326
00:30:06,734 --> 00:30:10,034
And yet, my dear Beechey,
as his personal troubles increase,

327
00:30:10,154 --> 00:30:12,998
so the quality of his painting suffers.

328
00:30:13,115 --> 00:30:16,619
- But still, the man can paint.
- For sure, he can paint a Haydon.

329
00:30:16,744 --> 00:30:20,123
The return of one prodigal
is worth more than gold.

330
00:30:20,247 --> 00:30:24,548
An essential quality for a prodigal, sir,
is humility.

331
00:30:24,668 --> 00:30:26,966
He is a cracked pot.

332
00:30:27,087 --> 00:30:29,465
He's heading for a fall.

333
00:30:29,590 --> 00:30:32,719
Gentlemen, are we as one?

334
00:30:32,843 --> 00:30:36,939
Sadly... I cannot give him
my support.

335
00:30:37,765 --> 00:30:40,268
He is not of our temper.

336
00:30:40,392 --> 00:30:43,236
Alas, the Academy
does not have need of Haydon

337
00:30:43,354 --> 00:30:46,608
so much as Haydon
has need of the Academy.

