371
00:34:26,869 --> 00:34:29,918
♪ Pop the question to Kitty

372
00:34:30,038 --> 00:34:34,839
♪ Pretty Kitty

373
00:34:34,960 --> 00:34:37,679
♪ The maid of the mill ♪

374
00:36:23,569 --> 00:36:26,743
- Good day to you, sir.
- Good day to thee.

375
00:36:28,156 --> 00:36:30,079
You be a lodgings, then?

376
00:36:30,200 --> 00:36:31,622
It be.

377
00:36:33,996 --> 00:36:37,717
- This chamber, 'tis available?
- It is, aye.

378
00:36:37,833 --> 00:36:39,506
May I peruse it?

379
00:36:48,343 --> 00:36:50,220
Mrs Booth!

380
00:36:56,810 --> 00:36:58,733
There be a gentleman.

381
00:37:00,814 --> 00:37:03,818
- Good day to you, sir.
- Good day to you, madam.

382
00:37:03,942 --> 00:37:05,910
- Are you seeking lodgings?
- Indeed I am.

383
00:37:06,028 --> 00:37:07,325
Here, Mr Booth.

384
00:37:09,114 --> 00:37:12,869
- Your top front, 'tis available?
- Maybe, sir, yes.

385
00:37:12,993 --> 00:37:17,089
- May I peruse it?
- Indeed, sir, if you'd care to follow me.

386
00:37:18,999 --> 00:37:21,047
- You just come off the boat?
- Indeed.

387
00:37:21,168 --> 00:37:22,761
- The Maggie or the Billy?
- The Maggie.

388
00:37:22,878 --> 00:37:26,758
- Oh, 'twas early today!
- We'd the best of the tide.

389
00:37:29,176 --> 00:37:30,598
There.

390
00:37:30,719 --> 00:37:33,689
- This be my better most chamber,
- Exceeding homely.

391
00:37:33,805 --> 00:37:35,273
Oh, I do thank you, sir.

392
00:37:35,390 --> 00:37:38,394
You're looking
at the finest view in Margate.

393
00:37:39,603 --> 00:37:41,981
They do say this town
be the first place in England

394
00:37:42,105 --> 00:37:43,823
that the sun do reach of a morning.

395
00:37:43,941 --> 00:37:47,821
Now, all my linen is freshly aired,
clean and sweet-smelling,

396
00:37:47,945 --> 00:37:51,199
and I can lay a fire for you,
should you require.

397
00:37:52,616 --> 00:37:54,163
Now, sir...

398
00:37:54,952 --> 00:37:58,331
...my terms is one guinea for the week
with no meals

399
00:37:58,455 --> 00:38:00,503
or full board for an extra 15 and sixpence.

400
00:38:00,624 --> 00:38:04,629
And I'm afraid I do have to ask
for a small deposit and a reference.

401
00:38:07,589 --> 00:38:11,093
- Five pound'
- 'Tis my reference and deposit.

402
00:38:11,760 --> 00:38:14,604
Oh, I can't take this, sir.
It is far too much.

403
00:38:14,721 --> 00:38:18,476
Refund of balance on departure'
That suit you, madam?

404
00:38:19,393 --> 00:38:21,395
I do thank ye, sir.

405
00:38:22,437 --> 00:38:25,316
Well, I should introduce myself.
My name is Mrs Booth.

406
00:38:25,440 --> 00:38:28,239
- And you, sir?
- Beg your pardon?

407
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:30,613
- I was asking your name, sir.
- Mallard.

408
00:38:30,737 --> 00:38:32,785
Oh... Mr Mallard.

409
00:38:32,906 --> 00:38:36,035
Well, I do hope you'll be
most comfortable here, Mr Mallard.

410
00:38:36,159 --> 00:38:38,253
Now, is there anything else
I can provide for you?

411
00:38:38,370 --> 00:38:41,249
A small bowl of water, madam,
if you'd be so kind.

412
00:38:41,373 --> 00:38:44,877
- Might that be a glass of water?
- No, a bowl.

413
00:38:45,669 --> 00:38:49,264
Very well, sir.
I shall bring that up for you.

414
00:39:04,813 --> 00:39:06,235
Yes?

415
00:39:08,442 --> 00:39:11,787
I found you a small bowl, sir.
I hope this do suit your requirements.

416
00:39:11,903 --> 00:39:12,825
Indeed.

417
00:39:12,946 --> 00:39:14,706
Where would you like
I should put it for you?

418
00:39:14,823 --> 00:39:17,667
Upon the window sill,
if you'd be so kind.

419
00:39:18,952 --> 00:39:22,957
Good. Oh, dear!
Do be coming along blowing now.

420
00:39:23,081 --> 00:39:27,882
Well... I shall serve your supper downstairs
in the parlour at six of the clock.

421
00:39:28,003 --> 00:39:29,923
And if you ever feel the need
of a bit of company

422
00:39:30,005 --> 00:39:32,724
you'd be more than welcome
to join Mr Booth and I in our kitchen.

423
00:39:32,841 --> 00:39:36,061
- I would not wish to impose, madam.
- Oh, not at all, Mr Mallard.

424
00:39:36,178 --> 00:39:38,601
We should be glad of your company.

425
00:39:57,949 --> 00:40:00,998
- I'll top up your ale, Mr Mallard,
- Thank you kindly, madam.

426
00:40:01,119 --> 00:40:03,042
- I hope you're enjoying your supper.
- Mm.

427
00:40:03,163 --> 00:40:04,710
Oh, good,

428
00:40:04,831 --> 00:40:08,051
Some folk do find shackles
loo salty for their taste.

429
00:40:08,168 --> 00:40:10,762
Can never be loo salty for me, madam.

430
00:40:11,588 --> 00:40:13,010
Oh!

431
00:40:31,650 --> 00:40:33,243
There, Mr Mallard.
This'll warm you up.

432
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:35,362
No, no, you sit yourself down.

433
00:40:35,487 --> 00:40:38,787
I can squeeze around here
just about these days.

434
00:40:38,907 --> 00:40:41,831
- So, you had a good walk, then?
- As far as Broadstairs and back.

435
00:40:41,952 --> 00:40:45,673
Oh, dear! That is a long way.
You'll sleep well tonight.

436
00:40:45,789 --> 00:40:47,291
Your very good health, madam, sir.

437
00:40:47,415 --> 00:40:50,510
- Very good health to you too, sir.
- Will you not take a drink yourself?

438
00:40:50,627 --> 00:40:53,176
I ain't touched a drop
this many a long year.

439
00:40:53,296 --> 00:40:55,719
He did used to enjoy a tipple,
though that were long before I knew him.

440
00:40:55,841 --> 00:40:58,515
- Man of the sea?
- He was, weren't he?

441
00:40:58,635 --> 00:41:02,435
- Ship's carpenter.
- Carpenter? Noble craft.

442
00:41:02,556 --> 00:41:04,229
What'd you ply?

443
00:41:04,349 --> 00:41:06,351
Whalers? Spicers?

444
00:41:06,476 --> 00:41:08,399
- Traders?
- Slavers.

445
00:41:09,521 --> 00:41:12,400
- For my sins.
- He don't like to talk about it, though.

446
00:41:13,692 --> 00:41:17,572
Africa, Zanzibar, the Indies.

447
00:41:17,696 --> 00:41:19,790
Such terrible sufferings I did see.

448
00:41:19,906 --> 00:41:22,125
Treated like animals, they was.

449
00:41:22,242 --> 00:41:24,165
Worse than.

450
00:41:24,286 --> 00:41:26,129
The howling sound of sorrow.

451
00:41:26,246 --> 00:41:27,668
Yes.

452
00:41:28,832 --> 00:41:32,257
- Changed my life, it did.
- Oh, it did there.

453
00:41:32,377 --> 00:41:35,426
- Led me back to chapel.
- Mm... hm!

454
00:41:38,091 --> 00:41:39,513
Humans.

455
00:41:40,177 --> 00:41:42,680
Humans can be dreadful cruel.

456
00:41:43,597 --> 00:41:47,647
I watch them boys down there in the sands
whipping them poor donkeys.

457
00:41:48,226 --> 00:41:50,320
Mind you, you're better off being a donkey

458
00:41:50,437 --> 00:41:53,281
than them wretched souls
on the slave ships.

459
00:41:57,777 --> 00:42:00,656
So, are you familiar with Margate,
Mr Mallard?

460
00:42:00,780 --> 00:42:01,747
As a boy.

461
00:42:01,865 --> 00:42:03,583
Oh, there.
You come here on your holidays, then?

462
00:42:03,700 --> 00:42:05,668
Schooling, two years.

463
00:42:05,785 --> 00:42:09,335
Oh, yes, Margate be famous for its schools.

464
00:42:09,456 --> 00:42:11,879
- Coleman's.
- Oh.

465
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:13,377
Mr Coleman?
I do remember he.

466
00:42:13,501 --> 00:42:16,220
- Up there by the Dane.
- Back of the old town.

467
00:42:20,258 --> 00:42:22,807
I lost two dear friends.

468
00:42:22,928 --> 00:42:26,102
- I am sorry.
- Scrofula.

469
00:42:26,223 --> 00:42:30,478
- Oh, yes. Terrible sickness.
- Aye.

470
00:42:35,398 --> 00:42:37,400
Longtime ago.

471
00:42:53,416 --> 00:42:57,296
- Oh! Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon, madam.

472
00:42:57,837 --> 00:43:01,216
- It is Mrs Somerville.
- Yes, you are expected.

473
00:43:01,341 --> 00:43:03,343
Thank you most kindly.

474
00:43:03,843 --> 00:43:06,687
Oh, what an elegant residence.

475
00:43:07,764 --> 00:43:09,983
Have you come far, Mrs Somerville?

476
00:43:10,100 --> 00:43:13,695
Oh, yes, indeed.
All the way from Chelsea.

477
00:43:13,812 --> 00:43:16,156
I took the steamer to Westminster,
about an hour.

478
00:43:16,273 --> 00:43:19,243
- Was the river busy?
- Extremely.

479
00:43:19,359 --> 00:43:22,078
You can see the whole world
on the Thames.

480
00:43:22,195 --> 00:43:24,948
- Mrs Somerville.
- Oh, good afternoon, Mr Turner.

481
00:43:25,073 --> 00:43:27,292
My apologies if I have forced you
to wait upon me.

482
00:43:27,409 --> 00:43:32,131
Oh, not at all. I have enjoyed
a most pleasant interlude with your father.

483
00:43:32,247 --> 00:43:35,171
- You find yourself well?
- Passing fair, thank you. And you?

484
00:43:35,292 --> 00:43:37,590
Indeed. Dr Somerville likewise?

485
00:43:37,711 --> 00:43:42,683
Oh, yes, he's much engaged
in administering to the poor veterans.

486
00:43:43,300 --> 00:43:45,428
Well, now, it's a beautiful sunny day,

487
00:43:45,552 --> 00:43:48,396
just perfect for our experiment.

488
00:43:48,513 --> 00:43:50,607
I have everything I need
here in my wee bag,

489
00:43:50,724 --> 00:43:52,818
Are we going to witness an explosion?

490
00:43:52,934 --> 00:43:54,732
Oh, goodness me!
No, I hope not.

491
00:43:54,853 --> 00:43:56,730
I'm astounded
you have all your paraphernalia

492
00:43:56,855 --> 00:44:00,029
- contained in yon small pouch.
- Indeed it is, Mr Turner.

493
00:44:00,150 --> 00:44:02,073
Everything except God's good sunlight.

494
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:05,823
Daddy, Mrs Somerville
is a natural philosopher.

495
00:44:05,947 --> 00:44:09,997
- Is she, now?
- Mathematician, astronomer, geologist.

496
00:44:10,118 --> 00:44:12,871
The universe is a wondrous thing,
is it not, Mr Turner?

497
00:44:12,996 --> 00:44:14,623
It is, to be sure.

498
00:44:14,748 --> 00:44:16,170
The planets and the stars,

499
00:44:16,291 --> 00:44:18,339
the oceans and the tides,

500
00:44:18,501 --> 00:44:20,879
the clouds and the air,

501
00:44:21,004 --> 00:44:23,098
mountains, volcanoes...

502
00:44:23,214 --> 00:44:25,888
The tides be subject
to the effect of the moon.

503
00:44:26,009 --> 00:44:29,889
Quite so,
the mysterious force of gravity.

504
00:44:30,013 --> 00:44:31,981
It is my strong belief

505
00:44:32,807 --> 00:44:35,481
that all things on this earth
are connected.

506
00:44:36,686 --> 00:44:39,610
- Nothing exists in isolation.
- Indeed.

507
00:44:41,024 --> 00:44:44,494
The rain falls, the sun shines

508
00:44:44,611 --> 00:44:46,534
and the onions grow.

509
00:44:46,654 --> 00:44:47,701
Oh, yes,

510
00:44:47,822 --> 00:44:50,245
Daddy likes to affect the pretence
of being a dunce.

511
00:44:50,367 --> 00:44:51,887
He is in fact a man of high intellect.

512
00:44:51,951 --> 00:44:54,670
- He taught me how to read and write.
- Is that so?

513
00:44:54,788 --> 00:44:59,385
- Education is an important thing.
- It is indeed, most important for everyone.

514
00:44:59,501 --> 00:45:03,051
I myself am presently engaged
in the tutoring of my children.

515
00:45:03,171 --> 00:45:04,718
That is indeed commendable.

516
00:45:04,839 --> 00:45:07,092
It is a privilege
that was not afforded to me.

517
00:45:07,217 --> 00:45:10,266
I am an uneducated,
self-taught Scotch woman.

518
00:45:11,137 --> 00:45:13,640
Mrs Somerville, you are what you are.

519
00:45:13,765 --> 00:45:15,642
- As are we, Daddy.
- True.

520
00:45:15,767 --> 00:45:17,314
Thank you.

521
00:45:18,812 --> 00:45:20,689
And what was your profession, Mr Turner?

522
00:45:20,814 --> 00:45:23,067
Daddy was the finest barber
in Covent Garden.

523
00:45:23,191 --> 00:45:25,410
I had some success in the business.

524
00:45:25,568 --> 00:45:26,785
Wig maker.

525
00:45:26,903 --> 00:45:29,497
He was a master
of the razor and the brush.

526
00:45:29,614 --> 00:45:31,616
You're the master of the brush now,
Mr Turner.

527
00:45:31,741 --> 00:45:32,833
Well...

528
00:45:32,951 --> 00:45:35,420
My little lad could draw
afore he could read and write.

529
00:45:35,537 --> 00:45:38,586
Sat in the corner of the shop,
scratching away with the chalk and charcoal.

530
00:45:39,207 --> 00:45:40,800
I'd stick his pictures in the window.

531
00:45:40,917 --> 00:45:42,169
And sell 'em, all of 'em.

532
00:45:42,293 --> 00:45:44,546
For two or three shillings apiece
on occasion.

533
00:45:45,255 --> 00:45:46,928
Do you have children yourself, Mr Turner?

534
00:45:47,048 --> 00:45:49,301
I do not, Mrs Somerville.

535
00:45:54,055 --> 00:45:55,898
Thank you, Mr Turner.

536
00:45:56,808 --> 00:45:59,106
- Have you ever seen a prism?
- I have not.

537
00:45:59,227 --> 00:46:00,649
Ooh!

538
00:46:01,855 --> 00:46:03,448
There it is.

539
00:46:05,108 --> 00:46:07,736
That is a thing of beauty.

540
00:46:07,861 --> 00:46:11,707
Shortly you shall witness
a rainbow passing through it.

541
00:46:11,823 --> 00:46:14,872
- Sir Isaac Newton, Daddy.
- Ah!

542
00:46:14,993 --> 00:46:18,873
Gentlemen, might I request
that you close the shutters, please?

543
00:46:18,997 --> 00:46:20,840
- Daddy.
- Ah!

544
00:46:23,460 --> 00:46:26,259
Tell us when to cease,
Mrs Somerville.

545
00:46:27,255 --> 00:46:29,804
We need to create an aperture...

546
00:46:31,050 --> 00:46:33,223
...to strengthen the colours.

547
00:46:36,306 --> 00:46:37,558
- There.
- Daddy!

548
00:46:37,682 --> 00:46:40,936
- Aha!
- Let us put the paper in place.

549
00:46:41,060 --> 00:46:44,690
- Daddy, some tacks for Mrs Somerville.
- No, no tacks, Mr Turner.

550
00:46:44,814 --> 00:46:47,442
The metal could contaminate the experiment.

551
00:46:49,360 --> 00:46:51,454
A wee nub of wax.

552
00:46:56,367 --> 00:46:57,664
Paper.

553
00:46:58,828 --> 00:47:00,868
And what is the purpose
of the small piece of paper?

554
00:47:00,955 --> 00:47:06,758
I shall cover the bottom half of the needle
so that it is not exposed.

555
00:47:06,878 --> 00:47:08,346
Ah.

556
00:47:10,590 --> 00:47:12,934
And what is it you are about now,
Mrs Somerville?

557
00:47:13,051 --> 00:47:15,804
You'll have to wait and see, won't you?

558
00:47:20,183 --> 00:47:22,527
Daddy, I wager that is the first time

559
00:47:22,644 --> 00:47:24,988
you've witnessed a hammer
being produced from a lady's reticule.

560
00:47:25,104 --> 00:47:26,822
For certain 'tis!

561
00:47:35,031 --> 00:47:37,204
You have the arm of a blacksmith,
Mrs Somerville.

562
00:47:41,287 --> 00:47:42,709
There, now.

563
00:47:44,958 --> 00:47:48,212
That has thrown
all those wee particles into chaos.

564
00:47:49,087 --> 00:47:51,181
Particles into chaos.

565
00:47:52,215 --> 00:47:55,685
What is the element contained
within the violet light

566
00:47:55,802 --> 00:47:57,475
such as magnetises the material?

567
00:47:57,554 --> 00:48:01,309
That is what, as yet, Mr Turner,
I do not know.

568
00:48:01,432 --> 00:48:04,356
- Ah, the majesty of mystery.
- Indeed,

569
00:48:04,477 --> 00:48:06,980
Now, let us allow nature
to take its course.

570
00:48:07,105 --> 00:48:10,279
Although we will have to adjust
the position of the easel from time to time.

571
00:48:10,400 --> 00:48:13,700
Indeed, as mighty Apollo moves
across his heavenly tract.

572
00:48:13,820 --> 00:48:15,288
Yes!

573
00:48:15,405 --> 00:48:17,908
- Three steps down, Mrs Somerville.
- Take care.

574
00:48:18,032 --> 00:48:20,876
Oh, my goodness me!

575
00:48:21,536 --> 00:48:24,210
Oh, Mr Turner, I am quite overwhelmed.

576
00:48:24,330 --> 00:48:26,424
Do as you wish, view as you wish.

577
00:48:26,541 --> 00:48:30,171
Oh, my!
These are breathtaking, are they not?

578
00:48:30,295 --> 00:48:33,219
My dear late father
would have much appreciated them.

579
00:48:33,339 --> 00:48:36,843
- A naval man, I believe.
- Indeed, he was a vice admiral.

580
00:48:36,968 --> 00:48:40,222
- We have the Battle of Trafalgar over here.
- Was he there, your father?

581
00:48:40,346 --> 00:48:42,849
- Er, no, he was at Camperdown.
- Ah.

582
00:48:43,808 --> 00:48:46,436
- Lord Nelson's ﬂagship, the Victory.
- Indeed.

583
00:48:46,561 --> 00:48:49,360
- It's a sketch for the painting.
- Oh?

584
00:48:49,480 --> 00:48:51,699
- Commissioned by the King.
- Is that so?

585
00:48:51,816 --> 00:48:53,818
Two years in the making,

586
00:48:53,943 --> 00:48:56,412
- He didn't like it.
- Did he not?

587
00:48:56,529 --> 00:48:57,872
- No,
- Too good for him.

588
00:48:59,949 --> 00:49:01,496
Two years!

589
00:49:01,618 --> 00:49:04,041
It takes me only half an hour
to paint a picture.

590
00:49:04,162 --> 00:49:05,880
So you are an artist, Mrs Somerville?

591
00:49:05,997 --> 00:49:09,968
Oh, I don't think we can quite use that term
in the presence of Mr Turner.

592
00:49:10,084 --> 00:49:13,258
Nevertheless, Daddy,
Mrs Somerville is a fine watercolourist.

593
00:49:13,379 --> 00:49:16,098
Oh, you ﬂatter me.
Oh, what an epic storm scene!

594
00:49:16,215 --> 00:49:18,764
Rock crushing a house in Switzerland.

595
00:49:19,594 --> 00:49:22,097
Calais sands,
women digging for bait.

596
00:49:23,473 --> 00:49:24,895
I don't care for that much.

597
00:49:27,352 --> 00:49:28,774
Oh.

598
00:49:29,979 --> 00:49:32,323
Oh, my! What have we here?

599
00:49:32,440 --> 00:49:35,319
Oh, it's Hannibal crossing the Alps.

600
00:49:35,443 --> 00:49:37,946
Do you see the elephant?

601
00:49:38,071 --> 00:49:41,496
- An elephant?
- He's in there somewhere.

602
00:49:42,408 --> 00:49:46,163
- Are you teasing me, Mr Turner?
- By no means, madam.

603
00:50:01,594 --> 00:50:03,221
Can you find him?

604
00:50:03,346 --> 00:50:05,690
Well, no, I cannot.

605
00:50:06,349 --> 00:50:07,851
There he is.

606
00:50:08,685 --> 00:50:12,030
- Oh! Ha, ha!
- Daddy's little jest.

607
00:50:14,607 --> 00:50:17,781
Oh, it is a terrifying scene!

608
00:50:17,902 --> 00:50:20,371
The elements
dwarfing the elephants.

609
00:50:20,488 --> 00:50:21,990
Hubris.

610
00:50:27,370 --> 00:50:28,792
There.

611
00:50:29,539 --> 00:50:32,383
Shall I make it do a wee dance?

612
00:50:33,251 --> 00:50:36,721
So, the end of the needle
that was exposed to the violet light

613
00:50:36,838 --> 00:50:38,590
has produced a magnetic north pole.

614
00:50:38,715 --> 00:50:41,093
- Like a compass?
- Exactly so.

615
00:50:41,217 --> 00:50:44,061
Whereas, Mr Turner,
had I done the same experiment

616
00:50:44,178 --> 00:50:45,851
using the red end of the spectrum,

617
00:50:45,972 --> 00:50:48,316
this needle would not have been magnetised.

618
00:50:48,433 --> 00:50:52,734
I have, from time to time, attempted it
with the green and the blue,

619
00:50:52,895 --> 00:50:55,944
and it has succeeded on occasion
but not consistently.

620
00:50:56,065 --> 00:50:58,284
Colour is contradictory.

621
00:50:59,110 --> 00:51:02,284
Well, is it, Mr Turner?

622
00:51:02,447 --> 00:51:03,824
Colour is absolute.

623
00:51:03,948 --> 00:51:07,373
Sublime but contradictory yet harmonious.

624
00:51:08,077 --> 00:51:10,500
You are a man of great vision, Mr Turner.

625
00:51:11,831 --> 00:51:15,301
The universe is chaotic
and you make us see it.

626
00:51:16,544 --> 00:51:18,262
In natural philosophy

627
00:51:18,379 --> 00:51:21,758
nothing can ever be proved,
only disproved.

628
00:51:21,883 --> 00:51:25,057
The purity of your prism,
the contamination of my palette.

629
00:51:25,178 --> 00:51:28,398
Natural light, blackness.

630
00:51:28,514 --> 00:51:31,518
White is the power of good,
black is the devil.

631
00:51:34,145 --> 00:51:35,317
Hm.

632
00:51:40,610 --> 00:51:46,367
Transparent bodies depend so much
upon what is opposed to them,

633
00:51:46,491 --> 00:51:48,243
having no colour,

634
00:51:48,367 --> 00:51:50,620
that they take every one offered.

635
00:51:52,663 --> 00:51:53,880
Um...

636
00:51:56,751 --> 00:51:59,721
Water often possesses colour

637
00:51:59,796 --> 00:52:02,925
but colour is not imparted
to its reﬂections...

638
00:52:04,008 --> 00:52:07,137
...or refractions
like a coloured glass

639
00:52:08,554 --> 00:52:13,230
when everything seen
is vitiated by that colour.

640
00:52:15,353 --> 00:52:19,153
Even the purest mirror
gives a tone to the sky

641
00:52:19,273 --> 00:52:21,492
and as the colour is increased,

642
00:52:21,609 --> 00:52:24,829
it destroys
all the colour of nature by its...

643
00:52:24,987 --> 00:52:27,240
...by its own dullness,

644
00:52:27,365 --> 00:52:32,462
while water often seems
to challenge the sky for...

645
00:52:34,956 --> 00:52:37,379
...brightness and...

646
00:52:37,959 --> 00:52:41,054
...and when possessing colour, um...

647
00:52:41,170 --> 00:52:45,346
...it's reﬂections of objects
appear more possible.

648
00:52:45,466 --> 00:52:49,221
In short, their effects
are like their qualities.

649
00:52:50,304 --> 00:52:54,104
One repels the immediate ray.

650
00:52:54,225 --> 00:52:56,068
The other absorbs it.

651
00:52:56,185 --> 00:53:00,031
The one transparent
while the mirror...

652
00:53:00,147 --> 00:53:02,366
...is opa... is opaque.

653
00:53:08,781 --> 00:53:11,625
How can they appear the same?

654
00:54:12,219 --> 00:54:14,938
Daddy, cease your labour.
Go and sit in your chair.

655
00:54:15,890 --> 00:54:17,312
I can't leave this.

656
00:54:17,433 --> 00:54:20,562
It'll keep for the half-hour.
Go and peruse your newspaper.

657
00:54:27,735 --> 00:54:29,203
Do not stoop.

658
00:54:33,741 --> 00:54:35,414
Go and rest your bones.

659
00:55:23,124 --> 00:55:25,218
- What's occurring?
- He's struggling.

660
00:55:26,502 --> 00:55:28,675
Are you rattling?

661
00:55:28,796 --> 00:55:30,548
Come on, bring it up.

662
00:55:44,520 --> 00:55:47,649
- Shh-sh-sh.
- No, indeed not, sir.

663
00:55:48,983 --> 00:55:53,580
I shall. I shall tell her.
I will tell her.

664
00:55:56,741 --> 00:55:59,540
I ought to have told her afore.

665
00:56:01,037 --> 00:56:04,166
- Years ago.
- Who do you speak of, Daddy?

666
00:56:04,290 --> 00:56:06,213
Afore they took her away.

667
00:56:07,626 --> 00:56:11,597
Eastertide, the good Lord took her from us.

668
00:56:14,800 --> 00:56:19,772
We did not do right by her, poor woman.

669
00:56:21,265 --> 00:56:23,063
She was a lunatic.

670
00:56:25,186 --> 00:56:27,063
We didn't have no choice, Daddy.

671
00:56:29,273 --> 00:56:32,698
She made our life a living hell.

672
00:56:33,652 --> 00:56:38,453
She was your mother.
Curse her!

673
00:56:40,826 --> 00:56:44,456
Show her due respect, boy.

674
00:56:45,664 --> 00:56:48,713
The bitch!

675
00:57:03,599 --> 00:57:05,693
My little lad.

676
00:57:08,104 --> 00:57:09,777
Daddy.

677
00:58:24,263 --> 00:58:26,891
- Good afternoon, sir.
- Good day to you, madam.

678
00:58:27,016 --> 00:58:29,860
- It's been a long while, ain't it?
- Mm-hm, yeah.

679
00:58:29,977 --> 00:58:33,572
- May I offer you a refreshment?
- No, thank you kindly.

680
00:58:33,689 --> 00:58:36,192
- Champagne?
- No, no.

681
00:58:36,317 --> 00:58:38,194
No mind, sir,

682
00:58:38,319 --> 00:58:42,540
I regret all my lovely girls are occupied
but we do have young Eliza here

683
00:58:42,656 --> 00:58:46,081
who I do not believe
you've had the pleasure of previous.

684
00:58:48,078 --> 00:58:52,083
She has a pleasing countenance,
when she smiles.

685
00:58:52,208 --> 00:58:55,052
- Good day, sir.
- Good day to you, miss.

686
00:58:55,169 --> 00:58:57,422
Show the gentleman
to your chamber, dear.

687
00:58:59,089 --> 00:59:00,636
It's this way, sir.

688
00:59:22,488 --> 00:59:24,240
Very fine.

689
00:59:25,032 --> 00:59:26,875
I do extras.

690
00:59:27,743 --> 00:59:29,541
No, no, no, no, no.

691
00:59:29,662 --> 00:59:31,414
Remove the bodice.

692
00:59:39,171 --> 00:59:40,889
Expose your breasts.

