704
01:01:12,139 --> 01:01:13,561
Twenty-two?

705
01:02:12,574 --> 01:02:15,168
Would you like
something to drink, sir?

706
01:02:18,580 --> 01:02:21,754
No... thank you, miss.

707
01:02:23,836 --> 01:02:25,383
Now...

708
01:02:26,213 --> 01:02:28,341
expose your breasts,

709
01:07:08,453 --> 01:07:10,296
- Good day, sir.
- Madam.

710
01:07:10,414 --> 01:07:12,291
- You be seeking lodgings?
- Indeed.

711
01:07:12,416 --> 01:07:14,510
Oh... I do know'ee.

712
01:07:14,626 --> 01:07:17,800
Er, Mr Duckworth.

713
01:07:17,921 --> 01:07:21,175
- Mallard.
- Oh, Mr Mallard. Of course!

714
01:07:21,299 --> 01:07:23,097
Well, you be lucky.
The room is free.

715
01:07:23,218 --> 01:07:25,220
- Splendid.
- Well, do come in.

716
01:07:25,345 --> 01:07:28,895
There. Oh, it be most pleasant
to see you again.

717
01:07:37,941 --> 01:07:41,320
Oh, Mr Mallard.
Everything satisfactory in your chamber?

718
01:07:41,445 --> 01:07:42,446
Most agreeable'

719
01:07:42,571 --> 01:07:45,324
Good. Well, you sit there
and make yourself comfy.

720
01:07:45,449 --> 01:07:48,498
I expect you'll be tired
after your journey.

721
01:07:48,618 --> 01:07:51,667
Now, I have not poured your tea
for it is fresh in the pot.

722
01:07:51,747 --> 01:07:54,125
No matter.
Suits me, brewed and stewed.

723
01:07:54,249 --> 01:07:55,751
Oh!

724
01:07:55,876 --> 01:07:59,676
Now, that I do remember, Mr Mallard.
